      <description>Game engine and 3D development MCP servers let AI agents create scenes, manage assets, control editors, and automate game development workflows through natural language. We reviewed 30&#43; servers across Unity (CoplayDev/unity-mcp at 5,800 stars with 25&#43; tools for scene/asset/material/script management, CoderGamester/mcp-unity at 1,300 stars with WebSocket bridge and prefab creation, IvanMurzak/Unity-MCP at 306 stars with 100&#43; native tools and runtime agents), Unreal Engine (chongdashu/unreal-mcp at 1,200 stars with actor/Blueprint/graph editing via C&#43;&#43; plugin, flopperam/unreal-engine-mcp with Flop Agent for autonomous world building, ChiR24/Unreal_mcp at 353 stars with 36 tools via native Automation Bridge), Godot (HaD0Yun/godot-mcp GoPeak with 95&#43; tools including GDScript LSP and DAP debugger, bradypp/godot-mcp at 58 stars with read-only safety mode and UID management), Roblox (official Roblox/studio-rust-mcp-server at 413 stars now superseded by built-in Studio MCP, boshyxd/robloxstudio-mcp with 21 read-only tools), web game engines (phaserjs/editor-mcp-server official at 26 stars with scene/asset/tilemap management, Three.js community servers), and game asset generation (Flux159/mcp-game-asset-gen with DALL-E/Gemini/Fal.ai support for sprites/textures/3D models). Unity leads in ecosystem size and adoption; Unreal has the deepest editor integration; Godot offers the most comprehensive single-server tooling; Roblox is the only engine with native built-in MCP support.</description>
